  <article>
    <h2 style="color:#69DC9E">Introduction</h2>
    <p>I take great <i>pride </i> in my sketchbook since I find it to be my safe space. There I brainstorm alot of my final pieces and even explore some meidums I am too afraid to try on a larger scale. I made this page just to showcase some of my favorite sketches from my sketchbook. <b>Enjoy!</b> </p>
  </article>
  
  <article>
    <h2 style="color:#69DC9E">Sketching process</h2>
    <p>When sketching, I don't follow a specific idea (or "metaphor") meaning that each page of my sketchbook gives off a different message and feel. However, one thing I try to keep is consitancy. For example, I draw many of the same elements multiple times, each time with a twist of course. Next, I draw daily or as often as I can. If not then I doodle aways.&#128512;</p>
  </article>
  
